    <h2><b>RULES AND REGULATIONS:</b></h2>
    <br>
    <br>
    <p>
    Rig the Market was created to help you learn how the stock market works by giving you RS 10,00,000 in virtual cash to practice trading stock online. The stock market practice accounts are real-time, realistic, and allow you to practice trading U.S.Stocks, NSE and BSE Stocks.
    When you register for free, you will receive a brokerage account with a virtual RS 10,00,000 in cash and you will be able to begin practice trading immediately. Once registered, you can also create your own contest and even invite your friends for group betting.
    If you are brand new to the stock market and want more help, you can get also learn about beginning investing with book by "Warren Buffet" available for downloads. Our virtual stock market will help you learn How The Stock Market Works, give you ideas on what stocks to buy, and help you learn the basic stock market terms.
    For any query regarding the stocks, user can visit the website bog and FAQs.
    </p>
    <br>
    <br>

    <h2>INVESTMENT</h2>
    <br>
    <br><p>
    Determine how much you want to invest. Since you are new to the stock market game, consider starting with only as much money as you can afford to lose. That way, if your initial attempt proves less than successful, you won't be out too much.
    Research companies in which you are considering buying stock. There is a feature called "LEADER BOARD" available to analyse top profit gaining companies worth investing and same feature also lists the companies that indulge loss that should be avoided to take risk of. To increase your likelihood of stock buying success, gather information on companies in which you are considering buying shares. This feature also enlists some top gainers and top losers of the game and the strategy and stocks they invest in.
    Purchase your selected stocks at the right time. Timing is everything when it comes to playing the stock market. To make the most out of your investment efforts, you must buy when stocks are low. Monitor the stocks that you are considering carefully, but buy when they take a slump.
    </p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <h2>VIEW HISTORY </h2><p>enables you analyse your trade history with accurate date and time.</p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <h2>WATCHLIST</h2> <p>allows you add some of your favourite company stocks to a WATCH where you can survey their complete pattern of ups and downs.</p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <h2>NOTIFICATION</h2> <p>gives you an alert when your selected stocks go above or below the set boundary price!</p> 
    <br>
    <br>
    <h2>PROFIT/LOSS</h2><p> gives you the facility of viewing profit and loss of the selected share stock.</p>
<br>
<br><p>
    You can also review and adjust your own private PORTFOLIO with entire game play.
    </p>
